President Uhuru Kenyatta and ODM Party Raila Odinga were among leaders present at the funeral ceremony of the late Mama Hannah Atsianzale in Malulu, Vihiga County. Mama Atsianzale was the mother of Amani National Congress leader Musalia Mudavadi. The 92-year-old passed away on December 28 while receiving treatment at the Nairobi Hospital. Other leaders present include Senate Speaker Kenneth Lusaka, CSs Eugene Wamalwa and Amina Mohamed, Governors Wilbur Ottichilo (Vihiga), Wycliffe Oparanya (Kakamega), Anyang Nyong'o (Kisumu), and Senators Moses Wetangula (Bungoma), Gideon Moi (Baringo), Amos Wako (Busia), Johnson Sakaja (Nairobi), James Orengo (Siaya) and Samuel Poghisio (West Pokot). Narc Kenya Party leader Martha Karua and Cotu Secretary General Francis Atwoli were also present. A requiem mass was held on Thursday at Friends International Centre Ngong road where close family and friends of the late Mama Hannah Atsianzale gathered to pay their last respects. Additional reporting by Sharon Maombo